            "metadata": {},
            "children": [],
            "content": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "metadata": {},
                    "children": [],
                    "content": [
                        "As far as I can think at the moment, the risk of this is that we end up with a “shadow router”, where for each route we also need a corresponding method in the plug. "
                    ]
                }
            ]
        }
    ],
    [
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "metadata": {},
            "children": [],
            "content": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "metadata": {},
                    "children": [],
                    "content": [
                        "I think this is a fine tradeoff, since there’s no way we’ll ever be able to automatically derive this information anyways."
                    ]
                }
            ]
        }
    ],
    [
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "metadata": {},
            "children": [],
            "content": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "metadata": {},
                    "children": [],
                    "content": [
                        "I made a new module under the namespace "
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "type": "inline_code",
                    "metadata": {},
                    "children": [],
                    "content": [
                        "Plugs.AssignMetaTags"
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "metadata": {},
                    "children": [],
                    "content": [
                        ":"
                    ]
                }
            ]
        }
    ],
    [
        {
            "type": "code",
            "metadata": {
                "language": "elixir"
            },
            "children": [],
            "content": [
                "defmodule MwwPhoenixWeb.Plugs.AssignMetaTags do\n  import Plug.Conn\n  alias MwwPhoenix.Blog.{Cache, Article}\n\n  def assign_meta_tags(conn, _opts) do\n    {route, _list, _opts} = conn.private.phoenix_live_view\n\n    assign_tags(conn, route)\n  end\n\n  defp assign_tags(conn, route) when route == MwwPhoenixWeb.ArticleLive.Show do\n    article = Cache.get(conn.params[\"slug\"])\n\n    assign(conn, :meta_tags, Article.build_meta_tags(article))\n  end\n\n  defp assign_tags(conn, route) when route == MwwPhoenixWeb.ArticleLive.Index do\n    assign(conn, :meta_tags, %{\n      \"og:title\" => \"mariovega.dev\",\n      \"og:description\" => \"A website with words about various subjects\",\n      \"og:url\" => \"https://mariovega.dev\",\n      \"twitter:card\" => \"summary\",\n      \"twitter:creator\" => \"@mariowhowrites\"\n    })\n  end\n\n  # default case, return nothing\n  defp assign_tags(conn, _route) do\n    assign(conn, :meta_tags, [])\n  end\nend"
            ]
        }
    ],
    [
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "metadata": {},
            "children": [],
            "content": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "metadata": {},
                    "children": [],
                    "content": [
                        "We get the route name from the connection’s "
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "type": "inline_code",
                    "metadata": {},
                    "children": [],
                    "content": [
                        "private"
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "metadata": {},
                    "children": [],
                    "content": [
                        " key, then match that in the guard for each iteration of "
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "type": "inline_code",
                    "metadata": {},
                    "children": [],
                    "content": [
                        "assign_tags"
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "metadata": {},
                    "children": [],
                    "content": [
                        ". This method does feel a tad brittle, as it depends on the structure of the conn’s "
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "type": "inline_code",
                    "metadata": {},
                    "children": [],
                    "content": [
                        "private"
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "metadata": {},
                    "children": [],
                    "content": [
                        " key staying the same across new versions of LiveView, but it works for the time being and provides a fairly readable structure to the code."
                    ]
                }
            ]
        }
    ],
    [
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "metadata": {},
            "children": [],
            "content": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "metadata": {},
                    "children": [],
                    "content": [
                        "Testing this runs into an issue: because we are no longer partitioning out each route into its own "
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "type": "inline_code",
                    "metadata": {},
                    "children": [],
                    "content": [
                        "live_session"
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "metadata": {},
                    "children": [],
                    "content": [
                        ", head values do not change as we navigate from page to page since Phoenix no longer knows this is something we need to do."
                    ]
                }
            ]
        }
    ],
    [
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "metadata": {},
            "children": [],
            "content": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "metadata": {},
                    "children": [],
                    "content": [
                        "For example, say we’re reading Article A. If we move to Article B, then look at our page’s HTML, we’ll still see the meta tags for Article A."
                    ]
                }
            ]
        }
    ],
    [
        {
            "type": "numbered_list_item",
            "metadata": {},
            "children": [],
            "content": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "metadata": {},
                    "children": [],
                    "content": [
                        "The primary reason to include these meta tags is for better sharing and discovery on social media. Since the crawlers for social media websites only need information from the first page visited (the page being linked to), we should be able to satisfy those requirements if the initial request always produces correct meta tags."
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "numbered_list_item",
            "metadata": {},
            "children": [],
            "content": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "metadata": {},
                    "children": [],
                    "content": [
                        "Separating each page into new "
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "type": "inline_code",
                    "metadata": {},
                    "children": [],
                    "content": [
                        "live_session"
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "metadata": {},
                    "children": [],
                    "content": [
                        " instances won’t actually fix any case in which one article links to another. Since we wouldn’t be changing base routes, Phoenix wouldn’t know to rebuild the meta tags and we’d run into the same issue."
                    ]
                }
            ]
        }
    ],
    [
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "metadata": {},
            "children": [],
            "content": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "metadata": {},
                    "children": [],
                    "content": [
                        "The solution as implemented will solve the immediate issue at hand, and I cannot think of an instance in which the way it isn’t optimal will make a difference."
                    ]
                }
            ]
        }
    ],
    [
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "metadata": {},
            "children": [],
            "content": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "metadata": {},
                    "children": [],
                    "content": [
                        "I’m wondering what a better solution might look like. I’m not sure that there is a means of updating meta tags that doesn’t involve a PR into LiveView itself. "
                    ]
                }
            ]
        }
    ],
    [
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "metadata": {},
            "children": [],
            "content": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "metadata": {},
                    "children": [],
                    "content": [
                        "We know that LiveView already contains one example of updating the root template in real time with the "
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "type": "inline_code",
                    "metadata": {},
                    "children": [],
                    "content": [
                        "page_title"
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "metadata": {},
                    "children": [],
                    "content": [
                        " assign. The question then becomes whether such an exemption should be expanded from a one-variable exemption to an arbitrary exemption allowing developers to register key-value pairs into LiveView. "
                    ]
                }
            ]
        }
    ],
    [
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "metadata": {},
            "children": [],
            "content": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "metadata": {},
                    "children": [],
                    "content": [
                        "Ultimately, I don’t think updating OpenGraph tags in realtime is important enough to warrant such an expansion."
                    ]
                }
            ]
        }
